    <updated>2024-08-14T15:57:27.837000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>ekp_shendi</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/584637</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;Dear Experts,&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;I am having a strange behaviour of some previously created BRF+ Rules, e.g. CHECK_BP_ROLE for the usage in MDG Change Requests. Our scenario is a &lt;EM&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Clean Client&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/EM&gt; and a &lt;EM&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Test Client&lt;/STRONG&gt; &lt;/EM&gt;on the same box, Transport Requests are managed thorugh SCC1.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;On the &lt;EM&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Clean Client&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/EM&gt;, the rule is deleted and cannot be found even in FDT_WORKBENCH, however on the &lt;EM&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Test Client&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/EM&gt; (same box as metnioned), the rules are avaialable and only marked for deletion.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;This leads to problems when excuting the rules during SAP MDG CR processing, resulting in the error message below on the &lt;EM&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Test Client&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/EM&gt;.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="ekp_shendi_0-1723643358024.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/151854i9E6008157CF352A4/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="ekp_shendi_0-1723643358024.png" alt="ekp_shendi_0-1723643358024.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Table FDT_ADMN_0000 is empty for the mentioned IDs in &lt;EM&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Clean Client&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/EM&gt;, but there are entries on the &lt;EM&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Test Client&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/EM&gt;.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Any suggestions? I have read similar posts, where the suggested solution was to delete the rules on the &lt;EM&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Test Client, &lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/EM&gt;which is not recommended as I would assume, and in our case not even feasible.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;I ran FDT_DELETE on the &lt;EM&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Clean Client&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/EM&gt;, but cannot run it on the &lt;EM&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Test Client.&lt;/STRONG&gt; &lt;/EM&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Any hint is well appreciated.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Best Regards&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Acram&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/old-entries-in-fdt-admn-0000/qaq-p/13794792"/>
    <published>2024-08-14T15:57:27.837000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
